         dkms (>= 2.1.1.2)
Recommends: linux-headers-amd64 | linux-headers-arm64 | linux-headers-generic
Description: Stacked tiering filesystem source package (DKMS)
 smoothfs is a native Linux stacked filesystem that presents a single
 logical namespace over an ordered set of tier backends (XFS-on-LV,
 ZFS, ext4, btrfs) and moves files between tiers based on access-heat
 policies. It owns no pages; reads and writes forward directly to the
 active lower tier's file operations, and placement changes are
 coordinated via a journaled cutover state machine exposed over
 generic netlink.
 .
 This package ships the module source tree and a DKMS recipe. DKMS
 rebuilds the kernel module against every installed kernel-headers
 package at install time and on subsequent kernel upgrades.
